title: Biggest Finales on May 14th
description: A list of the best TV series that ended their run on May 14th.

data.title: Malcolm in the Middle
data.description: This fantastic family sitcom helped pioneer modern television, ditching the standard multi-camera sitcom for a more movie-like single-camera setup. Plus it's hilarious and introduced the world to [Bryan Cranston](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bryan_Cranston).

data.title: My Name Is Earl
data.description: [Jason Lee](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jason_Lee_(actor)) plays the titled do-gooder in this feel-good sitcom set in a Texas trailer park which follows the recent lottery winner making amends for his life as a petty criminal. It's silly and stupid but shows a good heart.

data.title: Baywatch
data.description: Famous for its swimsuits and cheesy plots, this series was a trailblazer for direct-to-syndication television and helped launch the careers of [Pamela Anderson](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pamela_Anderson), [Carmen Electra](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carmen_Electra), and countless others over 11 seasons.

data.title: Dawson's Creek
data.description: The WB's flagship teen-drama set the stage for the likes of [One Tree Hill](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Tree_Hill_(TV_series)), [Gossip Girl](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gossip_Girl), and [Riverdale](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riverdale_(2017_TV_series)). Its four leads all had successful careers upon leaving, but they'll always be best known for their time in Capeside.

data.title: Roswell
data.description: Recently revived by The CW, this short-lived sci-fi/teen-drama may be most known for introducing the world to [Katherine Heigl](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Katherine_Heigl) of [Knocked Up](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0478311/).

data.title: Coach
data.description: [Craig T. Nelson](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Craig_T._Nelson) has starred in several long-running television series including [Parenthood](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parenthood_(2010_TV_series)) and [The Distict](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_District), but Coach marks his longest with nine seasons coaching the fictional Minnesota State University Screaming Eagles.

data.title: Family Ties
data.description: Before making it big with [Back to the Future](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0088763/), [Michael J. Fox](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_J._Fox) tackled the cultural change between the 1970s and 1980s for seven seasons playing young Republican Alex P. Keaton born to ex-hippie parents.

data.title: The West Wing
data.description: After the critically-acclaimed but eventually cancelled [Sports Night](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sports_Night), Aaron Sorkin hit big with this fast-paced ensemble drama accumulating [an absurd number of awards, including 26 Emmys](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_awards_and_nominations_received_by_The_West_Wing).

data.title: Seinfeld
data.description: With arguably the most famous finale of all time, Seinfeld will live on forever in popular culture and in syndication where it's made more than [$3 billion since 1995](https://www.vulture.com/2014/06/breaking-down-the-seinfeld-economy.html).
